      "link": "https://hongcai.163.com/thread.html?threadId=3501823",
      "unlocked": true,
      "content": "<p>The week started well, but there were a lot of late goals against us, like Germany's, and we can not be happy. A new week, and there is more information available now!</p><p>Argentina began the defence of their World Cup title with a 3–0 victory over Algeria. The biggest storyline of the match was once again <b><i>Lionel Messi</i></b>, who scored the first World Cup hat-trick of his career. However, the final scoreline slightly flatters the performance, as Algeria managed at times to challenge the reigning world champions before Messi’s individual brilliance ultimately decided the match. Note that Algeria did appeal against Messi after the game and is demanding a sanction for him: a suspension!</p><p>Austria, meanwhile, secured a 3–1 win over Jordan in their opening game. The result looks convincing, but the performance left plenty of room for improvement, and the full points would likely not have been secured without defensive errors from the opposition.</p><p>Betting. Argentina’s opening match largely matched expectations, while Austria’s display against a weaker-than-expected Jordan side raised more questions than it answered about the team’s true strength in this tournament. Argentina enter the match as roughly 65% favourites and are also likely to enjoy a slight crowd advantage in Dallas. Austria, who created few clear chances in their opener, are almost as likely to be held goalless as they are to score.</p><p>Looks likely, but the markets know that and the odds are nothing special.</p><p><b><u>Jordan v Algeria</u></b></p><p>Jordan left a positive impression in their World Cup debut, even though Austria ultimately took the points with a 3–1 victory. The tournament newcomer played fearlessly, created several dangerous situations, and remained level until the final 15 minutes. In the end, an own goal and a stoppage-time penalty widened the gap to a scoreline that did not fully reflect the flow of the match.</p><p>Algeria suffered a 0–3 defeat in their opening game against Argentina. The loss was expected, but the performance left a more positive impression than the result suggests. Algeria managed at times to trouble the reigning world champions and kept the match closer for longer than the final scoreline indicates.</p><p> Jordan showed in their opener that they are slightly more competitive than pre-tournament expectations suggested, but also exposed weaknesses, particularly in defending crosses and set pieces. Algeria are likely to target these areas in their game plan and enter the match as roughly 65% favourites based on their baseline level. If Jordan manage to improve their penalty-area defending, the match could become unexpectedly even. The expected goals total for the game sits at a relatively moderate level of around 2.6, which translates to the most likely results as 0-2, 1-2, 0-1, 1-3, 1-1</p><p>Good luck friends, remember to enjoy the football too, not only the betting part!</p><br/><br/><b>该文章通过有道机器翻译，仅供参考:</b><br/><br/><p>这周开局不错，但是我们在比赛的最后阶段进了很多球，就像德国一样，我们不能高兴。新的一周，现在有更多的信息！</p>\n<p>阿根廷以3-0战胜阿尔及利亚，开始了他们的世界杯卫冕之旅。这场比赛最大的看点还是<b><i>梅西</i></b>，他上演了职业生涯第一个世界杯帽子戏法。然而，最后的比分让他们的表现略显得意，在梅西个人的才华最终决定比赛之前，阿尔及利亚数次向卫冕世界冠军发起挑战。请注意，阿尔及利亚确实在赛后对梅西提出了上诉，并要求对他进行制裁：停赛！ </p>\n<p>与此同时，奥地利在首场比赛中以3-1击败约旦。结果看起来令人信服，但表现还有很大的改进空间，如果没有对手的防守失误，满分可能不会得到保证。</p>\n<p>押注。阿根廷队的首场比赛基本符合预期，而奥地利队对阵弱于预期的约旦队的表现引发了更多的问题，而不是回答了这支球队在本届比赛中的真正实力。阿根廷队以大约65%的热门率进入比赛，在达拉斯也可能享受到轻微的人群优势。奥地利在他们的首场比赛中几乎没有创造出明确的机会，他们几乎很有可能没有进球，也很有可能进球。</p>\n<p>看起来很有可能，但市场知道这一点，而且这种可能性也没什么特别的。</p>\n<p><b><u>约旦vs阿尔及利亚</u></b></p>\n<p>乔丹在世界杯首秀中给人留下了积极的印象，尽管奥地利最终以3-1的比分取得了积分。这位锦标赛新人无所畏惧，创造了几次危险的局面，直到最后15分钟才保持平局。最终，一个乌龙球和补时阶段的点球扩大了比分差距，但这并不能完全反映比赛的流畅性。</p>\n<p>阿尔及利亚在首场比赛中以0比3输给了阿根廷。输掉比赛是意料之中的，但他的表现给人留下了比结果更积极的印象。阿尔及利亚多次给卫冕世界冠军制造麻烦，并使比分接近的时间比最终比分显示的更长。</p>\n<p> 乔丹在揭幕战中表现出了比赛前预期更强的竞争力，但也暴露出了弱点，尤其是在防守传中和定位球方面。阿尔及利亚很可能在他们的比赛计划中瞄准这些区域，根据他们的基线水平，他们以大约65%的热门进入比赛。如果约旦能够改善他们的禁区防守，比赛可能会变得出乎意料的均匀。比赛的预期进球数在2.6个左右，这意味着最有可能的结果是0-2、1-2、0-1、1-3、1-1</p>\n<p>祝你好运，朋友们，记得享受足球，而不仅仅是赌博的部分！</p>",
